help_desc: This embed text contains all commands with detailed explanations
help_bcustat:
`Usage : _bcustat`
Display user statistics of BCU server with percentage data. This command will show number of human, members, pre-members, bcu-pc users, bcu-android users
help_checkbcu:
`Usage : _checkbcu`
Display users who have both member and pre-member roles or have none of them. Usually will be used for moderating server
help_analyze:
`Usage : _analyze [Files]`
Must be used with attached pack.bcuzip file. Under construction
help_prefix:
`Usage : _prefix [Prefix]`
Set your own prefix to make bot recognize your command
help_serverpre:
`Usage : _serverpre [Prefix]`
Set server prefix to make bot recognize user's command. Only **moderators** of server can use this command
help_stimg:
`Usage : _stageimage [Text]`
Try to generate stage image if it can. It will use BCEN font images if it can as default. `stimg`, `stimage`, `stageimg` are also valid command

`-f` : Force bot to use noto fonts whether it can generate image with BCEN fonts or not
`-r` : Generate image with BC image format
help_stmimg:
`Usage : _stmimage [Text]`
Try to generate stage map image if it can. `stmimg`, `stagemapimg`, `stagemapimg` are also valid command

`-jp` : Generate image with BCJP fonts
`-r` : Generate image with BC image format
help_locale:
`Usage : _locale [Locale]`
Set bot's language only for you. EN for 1, ZH (Chinese) for 2, KR for 3, JP for 4 (ZH, JP isn't ready)
help_helpbc:
`Usage : _helpbc`
Show all command lists which are related to BC

helpbc_desc: This embed text contains all commands which are related to BC with detailed explanation
helpbc_fs:
`Usage : _formstat [Name]`
Try to search unit with specified name, and display info of it. `fs` is also valid command

`-s` : Display info with second unit
`-t` : Display info with talents applied if this form has
`-lv` : Customize this form's level and talent levels. With order of `level, talent level 1, talent level 2, ..., talent level 5`
helpbc_es:
`Usage : _enemystat [Name]`
Try to search enemy with specified name, and display info of it. `es` is also valid command

`-s` : Display info with second unit
`-m` : Customize this enemy's magnification, can handle both hp, atk magnification. With order of `HP magnification, atk magnification`
helpbc_ms:
`Usage : _music [ID]`
Upload music with specified ID. Can be used every 5 seconds. `ms` is also valid command
helpbc_cs:
`Usage : _castle [ID]`
Upload castle image with specified ID. `cs` is also valid command

`-rc` : Upload `Normal Stage` castles
`-ec` : Upload `Empire of Cats` castles
`-wc` : Upload `Into the Future` castles
`-sc` : Upload `Cats of the Cosmos` castles
helpbc_si:
`Usage : _stageinfo [Stage Name]`
Try to search stage with specified name, and display info of it. `si` is also valid command

`-s` : Display info with second unit
`-st` : Apply star data, example is `-st 4`
`-stm` : Specify stage map name to be filtered. Must be used after specifying stage name first
`-mc` : Specify map collection name to be filtered. Must be used after specifying stage name first
helpbc_fimg:
`Usage : _formimage [Unit Name]`
Try to search unit with specified name, and display animation image of it. `formimg`, `fimage`, `formimg`, `fimg` are also valid command

`-t` : Display image with transparent mode
`-d` or `-debug` : Enable debug mode
`-f` or `-fr` : Decide frame of animation
`-m` or `-mode` : Decide animation mode | `A0`, `A1`, `A2`, `A3`, `A4`, `A5`, `A6`, `A7` are only valid mode
helpbc_eimg:
`Usage : _enemyimage [Enemy Name]`
Try to search enemy with specified name, and display animation image of it. `enemyimg`, `eimage`, `enemyimg`, `eimg` are also valid command

`-t` : Display image with transparent mode
`-d` or `-debug` : Enable debug mode
`-f` or `-fr` : Decide frame of animation
`-m` or `-mode` : Decide animation mode | `A0`, `A1`, `A2`, `A3`, `A4`, `A5`, `A6`, `A7` are only valid mode
helpbc_bg:
`Usage : _background [BG ID]`
Try to find background with specified id, and display image of it. `bg` is also valid command

`-w` : Specify width of image (Max 1920)
`-h` : Specify height of image (Max 1080)
